<tr><td><a href="#win049">049</a></td><td>Tidal K1 period</td><td class="v-selfcon">Self-Contradicted</td><td>Period is trivial (luni-solar diurnal); dome&#39;s local moon cannot produce K1&#39;s observed global diurnal inequality distribution</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="#win050">050</a></td><td>Tidal O1 period</td><td class="v-selfcon">Self-Contradicted</td><td>Period is trivial (lunar diurnal); dome&#39;s local moon at 2,534 km concentrates force at one point, not the gentle global diurnal forcing required for O1</td></tr>
<tr><td><a href="#win051">051</a></td><td>Tidal N2 period</td><td class="v-selfcon">Self-Contradicted</td><td>Period is trivial (lunar elliptical); dome&#39;s local moon cannot produce the observed two-bulge tidal pattern</td></tr>
